# Navigation Guidelines

## Navigation Architecture

实遇记 uses a bottom navigation bar with 5 main tabs:
1. Discovery (Tab 0)
2. Plan (Tab 1)
3. Camp Log - Center FAB (Tab 2)
4. Community (Tab 3)
5. Profile (Tab 4)

---

## Main Navigation Structure

### Implementation in `app.dart`
```dart
class 实遇记App extends StatefulWidget {
  const 实遇记App({super.key});
  
  @override
  State<实遇记App> createState() => _实遇记AppState();
}

class _实遇记AppState extends State<实遇记App> {
  int _currentIndex = 0;
  
  final List<Widget> _screens = [
    DiscoveryScreen(),
    PlanScreen(),
    CampLogScreen(),
    CommunityScreen(),
    ProfileScreen(),
  ];
  
  void _onTabTapped(int index) {
    setState(() {
      _currentIndex = index;
    });
  }
  
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      body: IndexedStack(
        index: _currentIndex,
        children: _screens,
      ),
      bottomNavigationBar: CustomBottomNav(
        currentIndex: _currentIndex,
        onTap: _onTabTapped,
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### Why IndexedStack?
- Preserves state of all tabs
- Prevents rebuilding when switching
- Better user experience (scroll position maintained)
- Slight memory trade-off for better UX

